  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense in most countries and is typically addressed under criminal legislation. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. It is usually prosecuted as a serious financial crime, with potential penalties including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n\nMany nations have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to detect, prevent, and prosecute such activities.",
